FBIS4-6773 "dreas079_i_94012" FBIS-EAS-94-079 Daily Report 24 Apr 1994 Cambodia Over 138,100 Hectares of Dry-Season Rice Planted Over 138,100 Hectares of Dry-Season Rice Planted BK2404142494 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network in Cambodian 1300 GMT 24 Apr 94 BK2404142494 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network in Cambodian 1300 GMT 24 Apr 94 Cambodian BFN [Text] According to the Agriculture Ministry, more than 138,100 hectares of dry-season rice, or over 86 percent of the planned target, has been planted nationwide by 4 April. Outstanding provinces and cities in the planting effort included Takeo, Kandal, Prey Veng, and Kompong Cham Provinces. The report also said that during this 1993-1994 dry season, our peasants planted 7,900 hectares of rice fewer than in the previous year. Many factors, such as [words indistinct] and late and prolonged harvest of rainy-season rice, delayed this year's dry-season rice planting. During the same period, over 50,000 hectares of dry-season rice were harvested nationwide and the average yield was about two metric tons per hectare.
